#: ../../../doc/en/reference/reference.rst:2767
msgid "Test Selection"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/reference.rst:2771
msgid ""
"Only run tests which match the given substring expression. An expression is "
"a Python evaluable expression where all names are substring-matched against "
"test names and their parent classes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/reference.rst:2776
msgid ""
"pytest -k \"test_method or test_other\"  # matches names containing "
"'test_method' OR 'test_other'\n"
"pytest -k \"not test_method\"            # matches names NOT containing "
"'test_method'\n"
"pytest -k \"not test_method and not test_other\"  # excludes both"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/reference.rst:2780
msgid ""
"The matching is case-insensitive. Keywords are also matched to classes and "
"functions containing extra names in their ``extra_keyword_matches`` set."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/reference.rst:2783
msgid "See :ref:`select-tests` for more information and examples."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/reference.rst:2787
msgid ""
"Only run tests matching given mark expression. Supports ``and``, ``or``, and "
"``not`` operators."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/reference.rst:2792
msgid ""
"pytest -m slow                  # run tests marked with @pytest.mark.slow\n"
"pytest -m \"not slow\"            # run tests NOT marked slow\n"
"pytest -m \"mark1 and not mark2\" # run tests marked mark1 but not mark2"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/reference.rst:2796
msgid "See :ref:`mark` for more information on markers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/reference.rst:2800
msgid ""
"Show all available markers (builtin, plugin, and per-project markers defined "
"in configuration)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/reference.rst:2803
msgid "Test Execution Control"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/reference.rst:2807
msgid "Exit instantly on first error or failed test."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/reference.rst:2811
msgid ""
"Exit after first ``num`` failures or errors. Useful for CI environments "
"where you want to fail fast but see a few failures."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/reference.rst:2816
msgid ""
"Rerun only the tests that failed at the last run. If no tests failed (or no "
"cached data exists), all tests are run. See also :confval:`cache_dir` and :"
"ref:`cache`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/reference.rst:2822
msgid ""
"Run all tests, but run the last failures first. This may re-order tests and "
"thus lead to repeated fixture setup/teardown."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/reference.rst:2827
msgid ""
"Run tests from new files first, then the rest of the tests sorted by file "
"modification time."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/reference.rst:2831
msgid ""
"Exit on test failure and continue from last failing test next time. Useful "
"for fixing multiple test failures one at a time."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/reference.rst:2834
msgid "See :ref:`cache stepwise` for more information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/reference.rst:2838
msgid ""
"Ignore the first failing test but stop on the next failing test. Implicitly "
"enables :option:`--stepwise`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/reference.rst:2843
msgid ""
"Resets stepwise state, restarting the stepwise workflow. Implicitly enables :"
"option:`--stepwise`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/reference.rst:2848
msgid ""
"With :option:`--last-failed`, determines whether to execute tests when there "
"are no previously known failures or when no cached ``lastfailed`` data was "
"found."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/reference.rst:2850
msgid "``all`` (default): runs the full test suite again"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/reference.rst:2851
msgid ""
"``none``: just emits a message about no known failures and exits successfully"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/reference.rst:2855
msgid ""
"Report the results of xfail tests as if they were not marked. Useful for "
"debugging xfailed tests. See :ref:`xfail`."
msgstr ""

